{"id": "EUVD-2025-32353", "enisaUuid": "22fb0a2d-f686-3f0f-80ea-3943d5ba4538", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Propagate error from htab_lock_bucket() to userspace\n\nIn __htab_map_lookup_and_delete_batch() if htab_lock_bucket() returns\n-EBUSY, it will go to next bucket. Going to next bucket may not only\nskip the elements in current bucket silently, but also incur\nout-of-bound memory access or expose kernel memory to userspace if\ncurrent bucket_cnt is greater than bucket_size or zero.\n\nFixing it by stopping batch operation and returning -EBUSY when\nhtab_lock_bucket() fails, and the application can retry or skip the busy\nbatch as needed.", "datePublished": "2025-10-04T15:43:43", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-04T15:43:43", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50490", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0e13425104903970a5ede853082d3bbb4edec6f3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4f1f39a8f1ce1b24fee6852d7dcd704ce7c4334d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/66a7a92e4d0d091e79148a4c6ec15d1da65f4280", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6bfee6eb3d6b96ae730a542909dd22b5f9f50d58"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50490", "GHSA-49r4-jvjj-q7x6"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "010d2af3-f1d6-35a1-b4ed-424ca2ebd8be", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "06a8a327-5179-351b-9417-a157662fe2b1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.3"}, {"id": "5703ab7f-9931-33be-82bb-443bfd2f8c72", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.17"}, {"id": "72102c00-d169-39af-bf1f-0864ecd9975f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.11"}, {"id": "91abbf38-e1ef-343b-abdc-b26419a0b665", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "20b6cc34ea74b6a84599c1f8a70f3315b56a1883 <66a7a92e4d0d091e79148a4c6ec15d1da65f4280"}, {"id": "b4de67d1-5f13-3fa9-adb2-67bd43e72815", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product